Privacy Policy

Last Updated: December 2025

1. Introduction Welcome to [Insert App Name]. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application.


2. Data We Collect

Account Data: When you register, we collect your email address, an encrypted password, username, and optionally, your Instagram username.

User-Generated Content: We collect content you create or upload, such as images for the "Buhtla Meseca" campaign.

Activity Data: We track in-app activities, including game results, coins earned, titles, rewards, and "Pekarski dan" progress.

Device Information: (Optional but recommended) We may collect basic device information (model, OS version) to ensure app stability.


3. How We Use Your Data We use your information to:

Provide and maintain the core features of the app (games, rewards, campaigns).

Manage your account and authentication.

Display your username and content (e.g., photos) on leaderboards or finalist galleries.

Send technical notices, updates, and support messages.


4. Data Sharing and Third Parties We do not sell your personal data. We use third-party service providers to power our app:

Supabase: For database management and authentication.


5. Data Retention and Deletion We retain your data as long as your account is active. You have the right to request data deletion. You can delete your account permanently through the profile settings within the app. Upon deletion, all personal identifiers will be removed from our database.

